modName: UNP BLESSED BODY UNPB - With Optional BBP Breast Physics
summary: Replaces the heavy weight UNP model with a larger breasted version. Not too crazy, but a definite increase in size. Now, thanks to xp32 featuring breast physics options.
descriptionHtml:
[IMG]http://i232.photobucket.com/albums/ee187/Raestloz/Description.jpg[/IMG]
The UNP Blessed Body increases the maximum size of the breasts for the UNP Body. The end result is comparable to CBBE in cup-size while still maintaining the details we UNPers love. Nothing is changed but the breast size, and the shape is still in line with the latest UNP breasts (B2), just increased.

Minor Update - I\'ve added a \"test\" armor. It\'s a preview of an armor I\'m working on. The weight slider works, and more important, it uses the Blessed Body tweak :D. Feel free to try it out. It\'s craftable under \"hide\".




[IMG]http://i232.photobucket.com/albums/ee187/Raestloz/installation.jpg[/IMG]

[color=pink][b][center]Installation  UNPB NMM Installer[/center][/b][/color]
Run in NMM, No other files are needed. If you would like another texture, there are a lot to choose from, UNP, UNPB. If you choose BBP version, you may want to run [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11811]FNIS 3.x.x -Always necessary files[/url] after installation.

[color=pink][b][center]Installation  Standard without BBP[/center][/b][/color]
First, [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=6709]Dimon99\'s UNP Body[/url] must be installed. Next, download the Blessed Body tweak and drop the data folder into your skyrim directory and overwrite when prompted.


[color=pink][b][center]Installation for UNPB-BBP v2.4  [/center][/b][/color]
1. Install UNPB-BBP 2-4 HD
2. If you don\'t like the texture you can install from any mod that support UNP textures
3. If you don\'t like Vanilla walking, then you could install [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=13272]Victorias High Heel walk Animation[/url] 


[color=pink][b][center]Installation for UNPB-BBP v2.2p, v2.2x  [/center][/b][/color]
1) Download and install [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=6709]Dimon99\'s UNP Body[/url]. Complete install, overwrite everything that was previously installed. Please also install Face texture compatible for UNP. this will fix seam neck issue. You can try Navetsea\'s, Coverwomen\'s, Bella\'s, or Oriental beauty UNP face texture. 

2) Download and install this mod last (UNPB-BBP). Overwrite UNP\'s files. 2.2x needs animations from a BBP animation mod.

[color=yellow]Optional - fore now has make integrated patch for CHSBHC-BBP arm fix which also will patch UNPB-BBP. You can download [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11811]FNIS 3.x.x -Always necessary files[/url]. Recommended to use it.[/color]

I install everything (ie: Place all files in file directory. C:\\Games\\Skyrim\\Data etc.) Overwrite where appropriate. If you use mod manager just make sure the load order remains the same 1,2,3 last.

[center][color=yellow][b]I\'m still confused, Is there any way to make it easier ? [/b][/color]

Try [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/20884]Configuration Package by sillumlt[/url] to make your life easier. Personally, I haven\'t test to use it

[color=yellow]\"Halp! My Orc Female isn\'t jiggling!\"[/color] 
There are a couple mods that change Orc race Females to use female animations. Try [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/25495]	
Orc female idle FIX[/url] or [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/16392]Feminine Female Orcs[/url] or [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/35155/]Correct Gender Animations by thefinn[/url]

[color=yellow]\"Halp! My High and Wood Elf Female clothing/armour CTD!\"[/color] 
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/33470/]High and Wood elf skeleton fix by drywater509[/url]

[color=yellow]\"Will this add muscles like in the picture?\"[/color] 
No. Muscles come from mods like [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=13377]this one[/url]. The UNPB Body simply increases the breast size of the standard UNP body. 

[color=yellow]\"I have a custom texture/normal installed, will this affect that?\"[/color]
Nope

[color=yellow]\"Does this work with skinny UNP?\" [/color]
no

[color=yellow]\"Will this clip with my UNP armors?\"[/color]
No. Armor meshes contain their own body mesh so using this as your base won\'t affect anything you wear.

[color=yellow]\"Are there any armors for this?\" [/color]
Yes and they are in the optional files section of this mod. xp32 is working on more ports, and I\'m building some new armors specifically for this body. 

[color=yellow]\"I installed BBP version but when I wear ____ armor my boobs don\'t bounce!\"[/color]
An armor has to be weighted and include the skeleton for BBP, which requires importing it to a 3d program and making it compatible. So only armors with BBP in the title will bounce.  

[color=yellow]\"I have some free time, interest, and want to help out. Where do I start?\"[/color]
I will provide full support, and answer any questions, for anyone willing to take the plunge of converting/creating armors. I know blender, and nifskope. I learned from the [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=3790]blender import-export tutorial[/url] on the nexus and the [url=http://wiki.tesnexus.com/index.php/Creating_an_armour_for_Skyrim._Part_1]custom armor tutorial on the nexus wiki[/url] and from asking questions of giants like dimon and caliente. And google.
